21:22.515 --> 21:24.982
I got three
stitches right there.

21:24.984 --> 21:26.384
Ouch.

21:26.386 --> 21:27.618
Yeah,
that's a good one.

21:27.620 --> 21:30.721
OK, and then I got kicked
by a horse right here.

21:30.723 --> 21:36.627
And then, you check
this scar out on my back.

21:36.629 --> 21:41.732
That is very impressive
dear, OK, you've been busy.

21:41.734 --> 21:43.200
Klutzy.

21:43.202 --> 21:45.102
You get
that from me.

21:45.104 --> 21:46.470
Do I?

21:48.207 --> 21:51.008
There will be plenty of time
to answer every one of your

21:51.010 --> 21:53.511
million
trillion questions.

21:53.513 --> 21:58.416
But for now,
just one.

21:58.418 --> 22:02.019
Where
have you been?

22:02.021 --> 22:04.488
Almost everywhere.

22:04.490 --> 22:05.956
Did you
miss me?

22:05.958 --> 22:07.058
That's two.

22:07.060 --> 22:09.660
Mom.

22:09.662 --> 22:14.999
So much you
don't even know.

22:18.271 --> 22:20.771
So you had
a boyfriend?

22:20.773 --> 22:23.107
Ha, no!

22:23.109 --> 22:24.175
No?

22:24.177 --> 22:25.509
No.

22:34.020 --> 22:40.725
Well, I almost, there's this boy
but he's not very right for me.

22:40.727 --> 22:42.993
Why?

22:42.995 --> 22:45.062
He's trouble.

22:45.064 --> 22:47.631
Trouble, isn't that what
being a teenager's all about?

22:49.969 --> 22:51.502
What's he like?

22:55.742 --> 22:59.443
Intense.

22:59.445 --> 23:01.879
Confident.

23:03.449 --> 23:06.417
I'm pretty sure he left a
dead racoon on the porch.

23:06.419 --> 23:09.453
I beg
your pardon?

23:09.455 --> 23:11.155
He did what?

23:11.157 --> 23:16.894
(laughter)

23:19.699 --> 23:23.501
I should try Dad again on
the CB and see if he's OK.

23:23.503 --> 23:25.736
I wish
you wouldn't.

23:25.738 --> 23:28.439
Why not?

23:28.441 --> 23:31.275
Try and
understand, OK?

23:31.277 --> 23:33.277
This is a lot.

23:33.279 --> 23:35.446
But he should
know you're here.

23:35.448 --> 23:38.716
I know, I'm just, I'm
not ready to see him, OK?

23:38.718 --> 23:45.256
I thought I was, but being
here, baby steps, OK?

23:47.193 --> 23:48.392
OK.

23:48.394 --> 23:51.162
OK.

23:51.164 --> 23:53.764
But wait, Mom,
you just got here.

23:53.766 --> 23:58.102
Yeah, no, I got a hotel
room nearby in Fairview.

23:58.104 --> 24:01.539
I'm not
going anywhere.

24:01.541 --> 24:04.308
I will see
you again soon.

24:04.310 --> 24:06.410
I promise.

24:06.412 --> 24:08.913
OK Mom.

24:08.915 --> 24:10.981
Thanks.

24:10.983 --> 24:12.082
This was nice.

24:12.084 --> 24:18.155
(music plays)

24:18.157 --> 24:20.357
I love you
my dear.

24:20.359 --> 24:24.028
So, so much.

24:24.030 --> 24:26.096
(music plays)

24:32.271 --> 24:34.405
Happy Birthday.

24:34.407 --> 24:36.640
Thanks.

24:36.642 --> 24:41.479
(music plays)

24:41.481 --> 24:43.714
I love you too.

24:52.091 --> 24:56.627
(music plays)

24:56.629 --> 25:01.765
So cake for breakfast, is
it everything you hoped for?

25:01.767 --> 25:05.736
You getting home safely,
that was the best gift of all.

25:05.738 --> 25:10.975
Yeah, so weird, snow
kicking up like that.

25:10.977 --> 25:18.015
And you here alone at
night, and you survived.

25:18.017 --> 25:21.485
How'd
you do it?

25:21.487 --> 25:25.422
Just kept
busy I guess.

25:25.424 --> 25:27.124
I'll get it,
you stay.

25:27.126 --> 25:28.459
You sure?

25:28.461 --> 25:31.362
Uh huh.

25:31.364 --> 25:36.567
I'm sorry I couldn't give
you everything you asked for.

25:36.569 --> 25:39.370
Your mother,
I tried, I really did.

25:39.372 --> 25:40.604
Her number's not
in service anymore,

25:40.606 --> 25:45.743
I sent some
emails, no answer.

25:45.745 --> 25:48.946
(music plays)

25:48.948 --> 25:50.681
That's OK Dad.

25:50.683 --> 25:52.750
(music plays)

26:01.394 --> 26:03.360
(music plays)

26:03.362 --> 26:06.430
(knocking)

26:12.471 --> 26:14.371
(music plays)

26:14.373 --> 26:15.506
What, how did you
know which room?

26:15.508 --> 26:16.574
I didn't.

26:16.576 --> 26:17.775
Let's go out.

26:17.777 --> 26:19.043
You're asking
me out now?

26:19.045 --> 26:20.978
Right now.

26:20.980 --> 26:22.313
And do what?

26:22.315 --> 26:26.083
OK, there's these kids at school
and they hang out at this vacant

26:26.085 --> 26:28.953
lot and drink alcoholic liquor
and indulge in youthful

26:28.955 --> 26:33.791
rebellion, so let's steal their
booze and set something on fire.

26:33.793 --> 26:37.094
Yeah, I think you left a
gift on my porch last night.

26:37.096 --> 26:39.897
I didn't want you
to forget about me,

26:39.899 --> 26:43.534
and jewelry is just so
gouache, don't you agree?

26:43.536 --> 26:45.302
What is your most
immediate problem?

26:45.304 --> 26:47.605
You not getting ready and not
coming out with me, come on.

26:47.607 --> 26:50.007
I can't just leave,
my Dad is.

26:50.009 --> 26:53.711
If my aunt catches me I'm
straight off to juvie,

26:53.713 --> 26:56.780
so you see what
I'm risking for you?

26:56.782 --> 26:59.984
I promise I'll bring
you back safe and sound.

26:59.986 --> 27:02.052
(music plays)

27:46.832 --> 27:50.134
(music plays)

27:50.136 --> 27:52.603
Oh my God.

27:52.605 --> 27:53.837
New guy.

27:53.839 --> 27:55.806
(music plays)

27:55.808 --> 27:57.341
I told them
you'd come.

27:57.343 --> 27:58.342
Hey Deb,
how are you?

27:58.344 --> 27:59.476
I'm Bronwyn.

27:59.478 --> 28:00.744
I know,
this is.

28:00.746 --> 28:02.546
Hey, you need to
meet my man Jay.

28:02.548 --> 28:05.349
He's got that busted motorcycle
you said you could fix up,

28:05.351 --> 28:07.551
remember?

28:16.829 --> 28:18.028
(music plays)

28:18.030 --> 28:20.130
Hey, you came with
Christian right?

28:20.132 --> 28:23.033
He's pretty God damn
hot, and nice, score.

28:23.035 --> 28:26.336
I'm Hailey, or Hales, or Hey.

28:26.338 --> 28:27.371
I know you.

28:27.373 --> 28:28.605
From where?

28:28.607 --> 28:31.809
I'm Arielle Ens.

28:31.811 --> 28:33.711
We were on the
curling team together.

28:33.713 --> 28:35.913
Oh my God, that
was like forever ago.

28:35.915 --> 28:39.016
Hi.

28:39.018 --> 28:41.251
Are you still
being home schooled?

28:41.253 --> 28:42.753
Does it
like suck?

28:42.755 --> 28:46.156
I'm super buzzed on this
maple cough syrup punch

28:46.158 --> 28:48.726
that Bronwyn made,
it is sick as thieves.

28:48.728 --> 28:49.960
Do you want some?

28:49.962 --> 28:52.663
Bronnie, get over
here you dumb bitch.

28:52.665 --> 28:54.732
She's my BFF.

28:54.734 --> 28:57.434
This is
Arielle.

28:57.436 --> 28:59.570
I know
who you are.

28:59.572 --> 29:01.438
Do you
know who I am?

29:01.440 --> 29:04.708
I'm Tim
Bateman's daughter.

29:04.710 --> 29:06.810
OK,
I don't know him.

29:06.812 --> 29:08.612
Yeah, well your
Mom knew him.

29:08.614 --> 29:10.047
Excuse me.

29:10.049 --> 29:15.619
Your mom knew my dad,
like on her back knew him.

29:15.621 --> 29:17.087
It was her mom.

29:17.089 --> 29:18.322
I swear I don't
know what you're.

29:18.324 --> 29:22.693
You need to get out
of here seconds ago.

29:22.695 --> 29:23.727
I don't know.

29:23.729 --> 29:25.028
Too late.

29:25.030 --> 29:27.765
(music plays)

29:27.767 --> 29:30.000
I'll wreck you.

29:30.002 --> 29:34.004
Ha ha!

29:34.006 --> 29:41.145
(music plays)

29:41.147 --> 29:42.179
(music plays)

29:42.181 --> 29:44.448
I shouldn't have left
you alone back there.

29:44.450 --> 29:47.785
I'm sorry.

29:47.787 --> 29:49.620
(sobbing)

29:49.622 --> 29:54.658
(humming)

29:54.660 --> 29:55.926
Hey, what
are you doing?

29:59.265 --> 30:07.337
My mom and I, we used
to write music and sing.

30:07.673 --> 30:10.140
It calms me.

30:10.142 --> 30:11.008
Cool, yeah.

30:11.010 --> 30:12.342
I play a
little harmonica.

30:12.344 --> 30:13.944
Oh that's great,
we should start a band.

30:13.946 --> 30:17.147
I really don't
care right now.

30:17.149 --> 30:18.816
That's fair.

30:18.818 --> 30:21.752
(sobbing)

30:21.754 --> 30:24.121
That girl said my
mom and her dad.

30:24.123 --> 30:29.059
Forget what she said, she's
a soulless wannabe bar star.

30:33.465 --> 30:36.033
Where is
your mom?

30:36.035 --> 30:39.636
She.

30:39.638 --> 30:43.440
She moved away.

30:43.442 --> 30:45.375
A long time ago.

30:48.013 --> 30:54.051
She wasn't, she wasn't
good at the mom stuff.

30:57.690 --> 31:00.157
She was an artist,
a photographer,

31:00.159 --> 31:03.327
musician,
traveled a lot.

31:03.329 --> 31:09.266
Even if, if that went down, it's
got nothing to do with you, OK?

31:09.268 --> 31:11.235
Hey, Arielle.

31:11.237 --> 31:12.336
(siren)

31:12.338 --> 31:15.205
Shit.

31:57.583 --> 31:59.917
Who's the girl?

32:05.090 --> 32:06.657
Who was
the girl?

32:08.661 --> 32:10.694
Calling the cops
was a bit extreme.

32:10.696 --> 32:12.462
You can't even
grasp how worried.

32:17.603 --> 32:19.336
Why did
you go out?

32:22.908 --> 32:25.475
Because he
wanted me to.

32:27.246 --> 32:31.381
No boy ever
looked at me like that.

32:31.383 --> 32:33.684
OK.

32:36.455 --> 32:40.891
OK, regardless I'm
still gonna have to.

32:40.893 --> 32:43.694
Punish me,
ground me, whatever.

32:43.696 --> 32:45.629
I know.

32:48.834 --> 32:50.734
I'm sorry.

32:55.407 --> 33:02.012
(music plays)

33:02.014 --> 33:05.983
I'm so grateful
that you're safe.

33:05.985 --> 33:09.820
If anything ever
happened to you.

33:09.822 --> 33:13.256
I can't even imagine.

33:13.258 --> 33:20.864
(music plays)

33:20.866 --> 33:23.700
(knocking)

33:23.702 --> 33:26.870
Come on,
it's freezing out here.

33:26.872 --> 33:31.241
(music plays)

33:31.243 --> 33:36.480
(music plays)

33:36.482 --> 33:42.986
(music plays)

33:42.988 --> 33:45.222
So, how in
shit are you?

33:45.224 --> 33:48.358
(music plays)

33:48.360 --> 33:50.427
I can't see
you anymore.

33:50.429 --> 33:51.495
Did he say that?

33:51.497 --> 33:55.298
I'm saying it.

33:55.300 --> 33:56.833
I can't.

33:56.835 --> 33:58.068
I can't do that
to him again.

33:58.070 --> 33:59.302
But that doesn't
mean that we can't.

33:59.304 --> 34:04.808
I can't trust
being around you.

34:04.810 --> 34:06.309
I'm not myself.

34:06.311 --> 34:07.978
(music plays)

34:07.980 --> 34:11.581
Maybe you are.

34:11.583 --> 34:19.556
(music plays)

34:19.558 --> 34:22.492
(music plays)

35:40.205 --> 35:41.771
Afternoon.

35:44.643 --> 35:48.311
That'll
be $4.50.

35:52.151 --> 35:53.984
And 50 cents
is your change.

35:53.986 --> 35:55.018
You have a
good day now.

35:55.020 --> 35:57.821
Thank you.

35:57.823 --> 36:01.158
Tim Bateman,
is he the owner?

36:01.160 --> 36:03.927
I suppose.

36:03.929 --> 36:05.128
Is he here?

36:05.130 --> 36:08.832
Could I talk
to him quickly?

36:08.834 --> 36:10.433
Sweetheart,
Tim's my husband.

36:10.435 --> 36:13.203
Passed away
some time ago.

36:13.205 --> 36:14.437
What was it?

36:14.439 --> 36:15.639
I made a
mistake, sorry.

36:15.641 --> 36:16.640
Who are you?

36:16.642 --> 36:18.875
I'm sorry.

36:18.877 --> 36:23.079
(music plays)

36:23.081 --> 36:24.080
Hey,
perfect timing.

36:24.082 --> 36:25.115
Can we go?

36:25.117 --> 36:27.250
I have homework.

36:27.252 --> 36:29.085
Where's your
lady stuff?

36:29.087 --> 36:30.420
They were out.

36:30.422 --> 36:33.490
Oh, are you
kidding me?

36:33.492 --> 36:39.796
(music plays)

36:39.798 --> 36:41.965
What is it?

36:41.967 --> 36:43.700
It's a joke.

36:59.351 --> 37:01.418
(music plays)

37:08.060 --> 37:10.460
(music plays)

37:10.462 --> 37:11.962
Before you say anything

37:11.964 --> 37:13.863
(screaming)

37:13.865 --> 37:14.965
What are
you doing?

37:14.967 --> 37:16.466
Let me out,
you psycho.

37:16.468 --> 37:18.001
I didn't want to spook you, but
I thought this was the only way.

37:18.003 --> 37:20.337
I'm sorry we got pulled over,
but I don't understand why we

37:20.339 --> 37:22.472
can't, I mean, I
really, really like you.

37:22.474 --> 37:24.274
No, you don't, you
don't like me, OK?

37:24.276 --> 37:25.675
The hell I don't.

37:25.677 --> 37:28.812
No, I'm a novelty, I'm a weird
homeschool shut in chick.

37:28.814 --> 37:30.413
Not to me
you're not.

37:30.415 --> 37:33.984
Oh yeah, what do you
like about me then?

37:33.986 --> 37:35.852
You just stepped
over the raccoon.

37:35.854 --> 37:37.387
What?

37:37.389 --> 37:39.055
You wanted to scream
and flail and freak out.

37:39.057 --> 37:41.091
You watched me,
are you insane?

37:41.093 --> 37:44.494
But you couldn't let me win,
and that moment I loved you.

37:49.468 --> 37:53.069
Yeah,
I was watching you.

37:53.071 --> 37:55.705
I can't not.

38:00.112 --> 38:02.612
How long have
you been in here?

38:02.614 --> 38:05.415
I figured farmers
get up early.

38:05.417 --> 38:07.250
God, you're an idiot,
we need to get you out.

38:07.252 --> 38:08.652
Not until you agree
to go out with me.

38:08.654 --> 38:10.420
That is the
hypothermia talking.

38:10.422 --> 38:12.255
I'm not leaving until
you say yes, that's it,

38:12.257 --> 38:14.524
so my
life's in your.

38:17.829 --> 38:20.830
Bluff called.

38:24.036 --> 38:25.869
It's the goat's.

38:57.436 --> 39:00.303
God, Dad,
you always do that.

39:00.305 --> 39:02.439
Sorry.

39:02.441 --> 39:05.408
Just had a
little accident.

39:15.120 --> 39:16.853
Lunch in 15.

39:16.855 --> 39:19.055
Yeah, I know.

39:32.738 --> 39:37.040
(phone vibrates)

39:53.392 --> 39:57.961
I just wanted to, we
never actually had

39:57.963 --> 39:59.996
the talk.

39:59.998 --> 40:03.733
(laughter)

40:03.735 --> 40:05.068
Seriously?

40:05.070 --> 40:06.703
Well.

40:06.705 --> 40:10.073
Dad, I'm eating
stew over here.

40:10.075 --> 40:12.142
You and the
Glancer boy.

40:12.144 --> 40:13.209
Christian?

40:13.211 --> 40:14.711
Are you and him?

40:14.713 --> 40:19.649
We had a very heavy make out
session in the cooler, yeah.

40:19.651 --> 40:21.751
OK.

40:21.753 --> 40:24.120
Always be
straight, right?

40:24.122 --> 40:27.090
Right.

40:27.092 --> 40:29.292
Well he's the reason
that you got in trouble.

40:29.294 --> 40:32.095
Dad, he made a huge romantic
gesture and risked freezing to

40:32.097 --> 40:33.930
death just to see me,
what am I supposed to do,

40:33.932 --> 40:35.698
not make out with
him in the cooler?

40:35.700 --> 40:37.534
The boy is dangerous,
I just don't want to

40:37.536 --> 40:39.436
see you make
a huge mistake.

40:39.438 --> 40:42.138
Isn't that what being a
teenager's all about?

40:44.009 --> 40:46.910
And can we avoid the talk,
because I know about the birds

40:46.912 --> 40:49.379
and the bees and the
condoms and the trees.

40:49.381 --> 40:50.780
The what?

40:50.782 --> 40:54.584
Nothing, it's just a clever
rhyme, Dad, let it go.

40:55.821 --> 40:57.987
OK.

41:02.260 --> 41:04.093
(knocking)

41:16.475 --> 41:18.842
Ever heard of
beaver farming?

41:18.844 --> 41:20.977
I mean farming
isn't really accurate.

41:20.979 --> 41:23.379
We breed them.

41:23.381 --> 41:26.616
Loan or sell them to customers
who want their creek dammed on

41:26.618 --> 41:29.285
their property,
stuff like that.

41:29.287 --> 41:31.754
I can't imagine
living out here,

41:31.756 --> 41:37.427
just so out of the loop
with the rest of the world.

41:37.429 --> 41:41.564
Why are you
here, Hailey?

41:41.566 --> 41:44.667
Bronwyn found out you
were at her family's store,

41:44.669 --> 41:46.703
you were snooping
around about her dad.

41:46.705 --> 41:48.571
God.

41:48.573 --> 41:52.175
So she's
super pissed.

41:52.177 --> 41:58.014
Like wants to
kill you pissed.

41:58.016 --> 42:00.683
Why?

42:00.685 --> 42:03.620
I don't understand.

42:03.622 --> 42:05.955
Why do you think
your mom left?

42:11.029 --> 42:15.231
My dad said it was
some kind of a breakdown,

42:15.233 --> 42:18.368
their marriage
wasn't great,

42:18.370 --> 42:21.170
she missed
city life, traveling.

42:25.510 --> 42:28.378
Tell me what
you know,

42:28.380 --> 42:30.880
please.

42:38.423 --> 42:42.225
Doesn't have
to be a race.

42:42.227 --> 42:44.360
Arielle might
be back soon.

42:44.362 --> 42:46.663
She'll ask
questions.

42:50.535 --> 42:52.635
And would it be the
worst thing in the world,

42:52.637 --> 42:54.837
if you tell
her the truth.

43:00.378 --> 43:02.779
Douglas is dead.

43:02.781 --> 43:05.014
Four and a half years.

43:05.016 --> 43:06.683
I know.

43:06.685 --> 43:11.921
The other day at your place
when I slipped on the ice,

43:11.923 --> 43:14.524
that was the
day I decided.

43:14.526 --> 43:16.693
Decided what?

43:16.695 --> 43:22.932
That it was time to
stop sulking in the past.

43:22.934 --> 43:26.869
I'm glad
you're over it.

43:26.871 --> 43:27.904
I've really
got to go.

43:27.906 --> 43:30.139
You can
talk to me.

43:30.141 --> 43:32.075
About her.

43:32.077 --> 43:34.611
Your wife.

43:34.613 --> 43:37.113
Why would I
want to do that?

43:50.095 --> 43:52.862
(music plays)

43:52.864 --> 43:55.064
Hey there, Mr. Ans.

43:55.066 --> 43:58.034
Dropping off more
dairy product, were you?

43:58.036 --> 44:05.475
(music plays)

44:05.477 --> 44:07.477
(music plays)

44:07.479 --> 44:09.612
Stay away
from her.

44:09.614 --> 44:15.885
Tell you what Dad, I'll stay
away from her, if you tell her.

44:15.887 --> 44:18.855
I'm around
like what, a week?

44:18.857 --> 44:21.991
It's amazing how many people
just offer shit up about you.

44:21.993 --> 44:23.760
Weird loner,
wife ran off.

44:23.762 --> 44:25.828
Keeps his
daughter locked up.

44:33.571 --> 44:35.638
(music plays)

44:42.580 --> 44:44.213
Gotta
let her go, Dad.

44:44.215 --> 44:47.216
Sooner or later.

44:47.218 --> 44:51.220
(music plays)

44:51.222 --> 44:53.790
So it's true.

44:56.094 --> 45:00.129
My mom and Bronwyn's dad
were sleeping together.

45:00.131 --> 45:04.434
And then she broke it off,
so that's why Mr. Bateman,

45:04.436 --> 45:07.170
you know,

45:07.172 --> 45:09.338
killed himself.

45:10.275 --> 45:14.711
He couldn't take it,
not being with her.

45:14.713 --> 45:18.448
Is this what the
whole town thinks?

45:18.450 --> 45:20.950
Could be bullshit
though, right?

45:20.952 --> 45:23.953
I mean,
so long ago.

45:23.955 --> 45:26.723
He's dead, and your
mom's not here, so,

45:26.725 --> 45:30.493
who knows.

45:30.495 --> 45:33.996
My advice,
just forget about it.

45:33.998 --> 45:38.401
Look forward,
life's too short.

45:39.738 --> 45:41.604
Yeah.

45:41.606 --> 45:46.142
(music plays)

45:46.144 --> 45:52.181
Thank you Hailey,
for being so nice to me.

45:54.586 --> 45:57.220
Avoid town, OK?

45:57.222 --> 45:58.855
OK?

45:58.857 --> 46:01.424
I mean Bronwyn's
my best friend and all,

46:01.426 --> 46:07.029
but she's crazy,
straight up.

46:07.031 --> 46:13.603
(music plays)

46:13.605 --> 46:19.475
(music plays)

46:19.477 --> 46:21.511
Yeah,
kids no good.

46:22.714 --> 46:27.383
Anything you can
tell me about him.

46:27.385 --> 46:31.120
Yeah, well how do you want
me to make it up to you?

46:33.024 --> 46:35.324
Yeah,
I read your ticket.

46:35.326 --> 46:39.295
(laughter)

46:39.297 --> 46:45.835
Well, I guess that I am
going to have to plead guilty

46:45.837 --> 46:51.274
and hope for
mercy from the court.

46:51.276 --> 46:54.210
(laughter)

46:54.212 --> 46:55.812
Yeah.

46:55.814 --> 46:57.613
Yeah,
that could be arranged.

46:57.615 --> 47:00.550
(laughter)

47:00.552 --> 47:02.618
(music plays)

47:16.134 --> 47:19.302
Hey.

47:19.304 --> 47:22.138
My precious girl.

47:24.042 --> 47:25.741
How much
time do we have?

47:25.743 --> 47:26.809
We have a
few hours,

47:26.811 --> 47:29.045
he's just in
Neville helping a client.

47:29.047 --> 47:30.079
OK.

47:30.081 --> 47:31.347
Where
did you park?

47:31.349 --> 47:32.849
Just
up the road.

47:32.851 --> 47:34.584
It's safe.

47:34.586 --> 47:36.719
I don't like all this,
it's like I'm lying to him.

47:36.721 --> 47:39.422
We don't do that
to one another.

47:39.424 --> 47:43.893
I know it's hard,
and I appreciate your trust.

47:48.800 --> 47:52.635
So dad did get a hold of you to
say that I wanted to see you.

47:52.637 --> 47:54.904
That's right.

47:57.675 --> 47:59.942
He told
me he didn't.

47:59.944 --> 48:01.844
Hm, well that's.

48:01.846 --> 48:04.180
Why would he say
that, do you think?

48:09.120 --> 48:10.853
This is your
father's house.

48:10.855 --> 48:11.954
I don't want
to disparage.

48:11.956 --> 48:13.055
Oh my God,
why is everyone

48:13.057 --> 48:14.891
pussyfooting around
me about everything?

48:14.893 --> 48:16.692
What do you
want me to say?

48:16.694 --> 48:19.295
He gets forgetful
when he drinks.

48:19.297 --> 48:21.497
Drinks?

48:21.499 --> 48:23.399
Dad?

48:23.401 --> 48:27.470
Do we really have to do all
this unpleasant business now?

48:31.409 --> 48:33.175
So what are you
trying to tell me,

48:33.177 --> 48:34.710
that my father's
like a secret drunk?

48:34.712 --> 48:36.545
Is that what
you're trying to say?

48:36.547 --> 48:39.315
All I'm saying is that when you
were younger, the second after

48:39.317 --> 48:44.020
your head hit the pillow he'd
be in the bottle or at the bar.

48:46.491 --> 48:49.458
I don't
believe you.

48:49.460 --> 48:52.929
If he's gotten
help, that's great.

49:04.776 --> 49:06.676
Did you have
an affair?

49:06.678 --> 49:10.846
Yes.

49:10.848 --> 49:13.149
And that's
why you left?

49:13.151 --> 49:15.084
What did
he tell you?

49:15.086 --> 49:19.322
He didn't, but apparently
the whole town knows.

49:21.292 --> 49:26.228
Everything changed when your
father and I got married.

49:26.230 --> 49:31.200
Before that, we talked
travel, seeing the world.

49:31.202 --> 49:37.373
And then, all he wanted
was to keep me here.

49:37.375 --> 49:40.042
I was miserable.

49:40.044 --> 49:45.181
Then you came along,
things were better for a while,

49:45.183 --> 49:52.855
but Tim Bateman and I,
we fell hard for each other.

49:55.093 --> 49:57.326
You loved him
more than Dad.

50:02.133 --> 50:05.001
But you
ended things.

50:05.003 --> 50:08.037
After everyone
in town found out,

50:08.039 --> 50:11.073
I humiliated
your father.

50:11.075 --> 50:13.609
Tim's family.

50:13.611 --> 50:17.079
I tried to make things
right with your dad,

50:17.081 --> 50:20.549
I went
back to him.

50:20.551 --> 50:22.818
But Tim,

50:22.820 --> 50:26.355
he couldn't
take it.

50:26.357 --> 50:33.295
They found him in his garage
with the engine still running.

50:33.297 --> 50:35.464
And who
was to blame?

50:35.466 --> 50:37.533
(music plays)

50:51.482 --> 50:53.549
(music plays)

50:58.790 --> 51:02.358
Is that your piece of
crap parked over there?

51:02.360 --> 51:04.326
Hello.

51:04.328 --> 51:08.097
You've got 30 seconds or
I tow your hunk of junk.

51:08.099 --> 51:10.232
That's my big crime
against my humanity, is it?

51:10.234 --> 51:11.834
Because I have a crowbar
in my trunk if you want to

51:11.836 --> 51:13.502
smash out
my tail lights.

51:13.504 --> 51:15.137
You're on a tight leash
while you're visiting here,

51:15.139 --> 51:17.306
Mr. Ross,
remember that.

51:17.308 --> 51:19.775
Huh,
you know my name already.

51:19.777 --> 51:20.643
Probably from
the other night

51:20.645 --> 51:22.645
when you pulled
me and Arielle over.

51:22.647 --> 51:23.913
You're on parole.

51:23.915 --> 51:26.082
It's my business
to know you.

51:26.084 --> 51:27.516
One more slip and
it's back to the city

51:27.518 --> 51:29.752
and straight into
juvenile detention.

51:29.754 --> 51:30.986
You want that?

51:30.988 --> 51:33.222
Is this his idea,
her dad?

51:33.224 --> 51:36.092
Did he ask you
for a favor?

51:36.094 --> 51:40.629
Or maybe you guys do
each other favors.

51:40.631 --> 51:41.864
She's a good girl.

51:41.866 --> 51:43.933
We all want her
to stay that way.

51:43.935 --> 51:45.201
Really?

51:45.203 --> 51:46.268
Because
from what I hear,

51:46.270 --> 51:48.571
she's not even
allowed off the compound.

51:48.573 --> 51:49.572
Farm.

51:49.574 --> 51:51.440
Tell me three
things about her.

51:51.442 --> 51:53.109
Three.

51:53.111 --> 51:56.112
Her name's Arielle,
I'll give you that one.

51:56.114 --> 51:58.747
